msg_object: %1: LSS/LMT: Node-Id out of range
Reason: slave repels node-number
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module

msg_object: Selecting a robot from within a triggeraction is not allowed %3
%1: External Error. Error Code: %2
Reason: error at module
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Stopping a called instance of routine '%4' was rejected
Reason: It was not possbile to stop routine with the STOP-statement because the routine was not started as a coroutine.

msg_object: Cannot write to sync value to sram
Reason: Can not write to sram
Effect: Sram data not up to date

msg_object: %1: Ethernet frame was received too late.
Reason: An Ethernet Frame was received too late, because either the EtherCAT segment is too big for the configured cycle time or the CPU power is not sufficient for the configured cycle time.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Solution: Reduce the cycle time or the number of slaves in the EtherCAT segment, if the EtherCAT segment is very big. Use a more powerful CPU, if the EtherCAT segment is small.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %2: Invalid update type (%1) for special tracking %3
Reason: invalid update type for special tracking
Parameter_3: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: Inertia parameters for tool %1 are physically inconsistent (%2-direction)
Reason: After transformation of inertia moments from the original coordinate system (cog) to the tool system (using parallel axis theorem) the resulting inertia moments are negative.
Effect: Calculated torques will not be physical.
Solution: Review the following parameters of the tool: mass, distanceCenterGravityX, distanceCenterGravityY, distanceCenterGravityZ, inertiaMomentJxx, inertiaMomentJyy, inertiaMomentJzz,  and inertiaMomentAroundCG

msg_object: %1: Program execution not possible due to missing operation release (active main mode: %2).
Reason: Operation release was not granted to the robot.

msg_object: Matrix addition: not equally sized matrices
Reason: Internal message: Matrix calculation with matrices of different size.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.

msg_object: Flashstate is critical.
Reason: Flashstate is critical.

msg_object: PLC-Interface not ready, stopping RC!
Reason: The PLC-Interface did not get ready during bootup

msg_object: Drive %1: not ready for operation enable
Reason: The drive can't be enabled, maybe because of a missing release-input

msg_object: %1: Fatal error in internal reference system administration %3
Reason: fatal error while updating Rc reference system list
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1: Drive %2 already in Standby-mode %3
%1: Ethernet frames were received successful again.

msg_object: %1: SDO (index: 0x%2 subindex: %3) aborted by server: 0x05040004 (CRC error (block mode only))

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Invalid identifier: '%4'

msg_object: %1: Drive-error launched (no errorcode available)
Orientation not reachable
Reason: Error during manual movement: Robot cannot reach the orientation.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.
Solution: Move robot to a different orientation.

msg_object: Spring stiffness for joint %1 must not be negative

Effect: Calculated torque model cannot be used.

Reason: Slaves with the same type (Vendor ID, Product Code) must define a consistent value or content for this node. The value or content of this node is not consistent for all slaves with the same type.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Solution: Make value or content of this node consistent for all slaves with the same type.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Release of non-existing write-lock. Object: %1 (ID %2)
Reason: Error due to an internal problem in the system software.
Effect: Context sensitive. Look at additional messages.

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0020 Slave needs cold start).

msg_object: %1: CAN in Error Passive Mode (Error Register %2)

msg_object: Velocity of cartesian position exceeds limits even if stopped on path at %1
Reason: The cartesian velocity limit is exceeded even if stopped on path at the given path position. This happens due to tracking.
Effect: It is not possible to pass the given path position without exceeding the velocity limits.
Solution: Increase the velocity limit or reduce the tracking velocity.

msg_object: Remaining flash life time: %1%.
Reason: Flash is in use for too long a time.

Parameter_8: Main run or in look-ahead problem

msg_object: Cannot read line %2 in motion file %1.
Reason: User error: Cannot read specified line in a motion file.

Parameter_4: configured limit of drive [units of drive]

Solution: Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.

msg_object: %1': configuration parameter '%2' is invalid (%3, %4)

msg_object: %1: short circuit/earth leakage. Error Code: %2

msg_object: Detected fan device %1 is ok

Reason: Input parameter for calibration function are wrong
Solution: Check checkboxes in the "Calc" tab of the result tables. Otherwise redo all calibration steps.

Parameter_8: Main run or in look-ahead problem

Reason: Mastering a Modulo Drive is not possible because they implement the modulo funcionality theirselves
Effect: The joint is not master and not homed.

msg_object: %1: SDO (index: 0x%2 subindex: %3) aborted by server: 0x08000000 (General error)

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Invalid range

msg_object: Programs can't be started/continued while the deadman button is not pressed

Reason: Not enough memory for Motion Control Unit. Perhaps there is an error in the application programm (objects are not deleted).

msg_object: %8 Joint jerk exceeds limit by %1 %%, wrist joint: %2; value: %3, limit: %4, motion command (%5) %6, parameter %7
Reason: A violation of the specified limit has been detected.

Parameter_8: Main run or in look-ahead problem

Solution: increase windows-task-priority or increase mcu cycle time

Force/torque of joint %2 exceeds limits even if stopped on path at %1
Reason: The force or torque limit of the given joint is exceeded even if stopped on path at the given path position. This happens due to tracking or gravity.
Effect: It could be possible to pass the given path position without exceeding the force/torque limits but it is not possible to stop and therefore it is dangerous to try to pass the position.
Solution: Increase the force/torque limit or reduce the tracking velocity.

msg_object: Type of Scara-robot is not yet implemented

Effect: Kinematic cannot be used. Motion program cannot be started.
Solution: Use different robot type, configure different DH parameters, or contact your distributor.

msg_object: No event handle specified for job <%1>

msg_object: %1: SDO (index: 0x%2 subindex: %3) aborted by server: 0x06040047 (General internal incompatibility in the device)

Solution: The active FB of the axis has to be called each PLC cycle.

Effect: If the joint ist not masked, the kinematic is stopped automatically.

PostmortemAnalyser cannot add Interface

If the error occured due to calling a FB MC_Power with Enable=TRUE the axis stays in the PLCopen state 'Disabled'.  If the next time the FB MC_Power is called with Enable=TRUE, the FB will be rejected with an error.

msg_object: Robot %1 is entering blocked area %2 with guard point%3 of %4
Reason: Robot is entering a blocked area.

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x001D Invalid output configuration).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. Sync manager configuration for output process data is invalid.

msg_object: %1: Homing program can't be executed due to unreferenced drives

Effect: The job is not applied to the second kinematic.

Parameter_3: Name of the kinematic to which the job has been tried to apply

msg_object: %1: SDO (index: 0x%2 subindex: %3) aborted by server: 0x06090036 (Maximum value is less than minimum value)

msg_object: %1.%2 Line %3: Prelimiter - %4%% of prog. velocity (SegNr %5)

msg_object: Mains power supply missing - Enabling drives for '%1' not possible

msg_object: IO-Timer: Cycle-Time of '%1' (%2us) not multiple of System-Tick (%3us)
Reason: Cycle time of configured io-timer is not a multiple of system tick time.

msg_object: No name configured for drive %1 (robot: %2)
Reason: The name for the drive is missing in configuration

msg_object: couldn't add to housekeeper
Reason: couldn't add to housekeeper

msg_object: %1 (joint %2): Invalid value for 'increments per revolution' (numerator: %3 denominator: %4)
Reason: An invalid value for 'increments per revolution' has been configured.
Effect: increments per revolution' is set to 1.
Solution: The numerator must not be 0 and the denominator must be greater than 0.

msg_object: %1: Robot not ready, movement not possible (requested mode: %2).
Reason: Conditions to move robot in given motion mode are not fulfilled.
Solution: Check system state (releases, drive state, pending errors, ...)

msg_object: Illegal config entry: '%1' - delete entry
Reason: Illegal configuration entry

msg_object: %1: '%2' is not a correct XML file.
Reason: The XML file is malformed.
Effect: The file could not be read and the operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.

msg_object: %1: McuMove failed %3
Reason: Call of McuMove returned false.

msg_object: %1: Communication lost
Reason: Communication with drive lost, maybe the connection has been interrupted.

msg_object: Transformation %1 (ID %2) uses an invalid reference system (%3 ).
Reason: Application error: A transformation uses an invalid reference system.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.

msg_object: Incompatible external tool %1 in motion command %2.
Reason: An incompatible external tool has been used in a spline command or a parabola command. The same external tool as in the previous motion command must be used.
Effect: The motion command cannot be appended to the path.
Solution: You can either refrain from changing the external tool or use another type of motion command.

msg_object: %1: Object #%2 was not found in order-list %3
Object with address %1 does not exist
Reason: Error due to an internal problem in the system software.
Effect: Context sensitive. Look at additional messages.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.

Reason: A unit is expected but the given identifier is not one.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: %1: repeatedly no cyclic data received
Reason: Some telegrams failed in cyclic process
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the axis

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Timer set with a negativ time

Effect: The signalization variable of SysTimerSet  ist not set.

msg_object: InversTrafo configured without activating ForwardTrafo
Reason: For a kinematic an inverse transformation has been configured, but the forward transformation is missing.
Effect: The corresponding kinematic is not available.

msg_object: %1: Mandatory slave '%2' not found (vendor ID = %3, product code = %4).
Reason: A mandatory slave does not exist in the EtherCAT segment.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Solution: Add mandatory slave to the EtherCAT segment or adapt configuration.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object
Parameter_2: Configuration path or name of configured slave

msg_object: No configuration data found for joint <%1>
Reason: Nothing has been configured for the joint indicated.
Effect: The corresponding kinematic is not available.

msg_object: Robot stops because of previous error; kinematic %1 (ID %2), motion command %3 (ID %4), parameter %5
Reason: This message occurs in the course of various different problems related to interpolation errors.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0018 No valid inputs available).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state. The slave application cannot provide valid inputs.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Check hardware- and software configuration of the slave. Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0037 DC Sync1 cycle time).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. DC sync1 cycle time does not fit to the application requirements.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.

msg_object: No inverse transformation available for kinematic %1 (ID %2)
Reason: For the execution of a certain command the inverse transformation of kinematic must be activated.
Effect: Cartesian movements of the robot are not allowed.
Solution: Check configuration data. Activate inverse transformation for kinematic.

msg_object: Kinematic %1: waiting for automatic mode... %3

Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: Application error: Invalid servo state detected by MCU, movement not allowed (state: %1, kinematic %2, joint  %3
Reason: Error in application servo logic

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): No structure
Reason: A structured type is expected, but the given is not one.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: Kinematic %1 (joint %2): Referencing using reference pulse: No master value available.
Reason: The position of the drive cannot be set by using reference pulse as there is no master value available.
Effect: The joint's position has not been set.
Solution: The drive must be mastered first.

msg_object: Configured number of passive base joints (%1) too big for this robot type (may be at most %2)
Reason: Configuration error: the configured number of passive base joints is too big.
Effect: Kinematic cannot be used. Motion program cannot be started.
Solution: Check the configuration data of the kinematic.
Parameter_1: Configured number of passive base joints
Parameter_2: Allowed number of passive base joints

msg_object: IO: Create IO-Timer failed
Reason: Installation of io-internal timers failed.

msg_object: Internal error: Kernel driver %1 (%2) IOCTL %3 failed, last error %4
Reason: error when executing kernel driver ioctl commad

msg_object: Not enough positions in motion file %1.
Reason: Not enough positions in a motion file.

msg_object: %1': invalid torque for homing sequence (%2)
Reason: Execution of a homing sequence is rejected due to invalid value of parameter 'homing torque'.
Effect: The homing sequence is not executed.
Solution: The parameter for the homing sequence have to be checked.

msg_object: %1: Couldn't detect last tracking position for object #%2 %3
Tool %1 couldn't be set, mcu-id (%2) is invalid %3
Reason: There was an attempt to set a tool with invalid mcu-id
Parameter_3: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1: Too many %2-PDOs configured (act=%3, max=%4)
Reason: Too many process data objects have been configured.

Parameter_1: Name or configuration path of the node
Parameter_2: Kind of PDO (RX or TX, controls point of view)

msg_object: Programmed cart. acceleration %4 (component %3) must be greater than 0. Dynamics %1 (addr. %2) invalid.
Reason: The application program tried to set the cartesian acceleration to a value near zero. This is not allowed.
Effect: The command for changing the acceleration value is not executed and an error occurs. If the application continues executing the program further errors will occur.
Solution: Change value for cartesian acceleration in the application program.

msg_object: %1: Klink (virtual) node address (%2) already in use (%3)
Reason: declared KLink node-address already in use
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module
Parameter_3: description of the moduleusing the address

msg_object: %1: ignoring new overlap settings for jog-path %3
Reason: changing the overlap not allowed for jog-path

msg_object: %1': invalid timeout for homing sequence (%2)
Reason: Execution of a homing sequence is rejected due to invalid value of parameter 'homing timeout'.
Effect: The homing sequence is not executed.
Solution: The parameter for the homing sequence have to be checked.

msg_object: Program: '%1' was reinitialized, because main mode switched to manual.
Reason: Main mode switched to manual mode.
the system-startup has finished

msg_object: %2: IMM input signal '%1' is not available %3

Effect: Requested operation can not be executed.

msg_object: Invalid servo-state for '%1' (stateword: %2, desired state: %3)

Cannot use automatic slot selection for device list %1. There is more than one matching device in the system.
Reason: automatic PCI addressing cannot be used, because more tha one device is present in list

msg_object: Kinematic %1: Cannot calculate reference system for path tracking at %2.

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Illegal use of BREAK

msg_object: %1: Device-Error
Reason: error at CAN-bus-device
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the Can-Channel

msg_object: Drive %1: Error launched (error-ID: %2) %3
%1: insufficient path default settings %3
Reason: default-overlap, -tool or -dynamic not set
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1: Joints area '%2' reached, last admissible position not calculable because of passive joints
Reason: A joints area has been reached during jogging. The last admissible position at the area border is not exactly calculable due to the passive joints.
Effect: The given joint cannot move any further in the current direction.
Solution: Change movement direction or check joints areas.

msg_object: Projectname %1 already in use
Reason: The project could not be created because the name is already in use.
Effect: It is not possible to create the project.

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0034 DC sync timeout error).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. Multiple synchronization errors. Too many sync manager events missed.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1: Jogging not possible, because generation of drive set values is not active.
Reason: Mc interpolator for set values is not running.
Solution: Start mc interpolator for set values.

msg_object: Started application %1
No memory available in matrix constructor
Reason: Internal message: No memory left for matrix.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.

msg_object: Position '%1' can't be calculated for robot '%2' (error code=%3)
Reason: The given position can not be calculated for this robot, the calculation returned the given error code.
Solution: Check and modify given position and contact your system integrator.

msg_object: %1: Mapping to process data ('%2') failed because of invalid length (%3, %4)
Reason: e.g.: The drive of the axis does not support multi cycle arrays.
Effect: The axis can not be operated.

msg_object: Area '%1' could not be registered, max. allowed number of areas (%2) has already been instantiated
Reason: Too many area instances.

msg_object: Invalid signal state given from IMM, '%1' and '%2' are set at once
Reason: Invalid signals from IMM.

msg_object: %1: Auto-key ignored since a program is running
Reason: A program is running
Effect: Pressing the key had no effect

msg_object: %1: Invalid cycle time (%2ms) for clock master
Reason: cyclic-time invalid for clock-master
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the CAN-channel

msg_object: Shared memory '%1' could not be mapped.
Reason: The shared memory cannot be mapped.
Solution: Internal error, contact your system supplier

msg_object: IO-Port %1 not created
%1: Invalid movement of axis %2 while there where drives in standby-mode (position deviation: %3, max. tolerated deviation: %4)
%1: Watchdog reset (%2, %3).
Reason: Reset by Watchdog.
Solution: Adjust update timing or contact manufacturer.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Call McuStopInterpolator() first for kinematic <%1>
Reason: Application error. Before executing a certain command it is necessary to call McuStopInterpolator().

msg_object: Tool couldn't be set, tool-index (%1) is invalid %3
Reason: There was an attempt to set a tool with invalid tool-index
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: Interface %1 of version %2 is not compatible with the installed Mc version (%3)
Reason: The Mc interface version that is used is not compatible with the installed Mc version.
Effect: No application program can be started.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor. Match the Mc-Interface and the installed Mc-Version.
Parameter_2: Mc version where the used interface stems from
Parameter_3: Mc version that is installed on the system

msg_object: Mass for tool %1 must not be negative
Reason: A tool has been attributed a negative mass.
Effect: The calculated torques will be wrong.

msg_object: Cannot read ShadowRtc from Eeprom
Reason: Can not read eeprom

msg_object: Kinematic %1: MoveToTarget is not allowed when the robot is moving.
Reason: Application error: A MoveToTarget command is not allowed when the robot is moving.
Effect: The command is ignored and an emergency stop is initiated.

msg_object: PCB Changed (part %1): funcVar: %2
Reason: Fourth part of generic PCB-Change message

msg_object: Kinematic <%1> (ID %2) not yet READY for command <%3>
Reason: Application error: For the indicated command the kinematic must be in state READY (call McuStartInterpolator first).

msg_object: unknown acceleration/torque
Reason: Additional information

msg_object: Internal error: Closing event %1 failed, last error %2.
Reason: interrupt event cannot be closed

msg_object: Internal error: Assigning access area for PCI device %1.%2 slot %3 function %4 failed (%5).
Reason: assignment of access area failed because of allocation address translation error

msg_object: %1: Emergency-Message from node %2: Error Code: %3
Reason: Node has sent an emergency message.
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of module
Parameter_3: Emergency message of node: emergency error (byte1, byte 0), error register, manufacturer specific error field (bytes 3 - 7)

msg_object: PCB Changed (part %1): name: %2, addr: %3
Reason: First part of generic PCB-Change message

msg_object: Cannot calculate Restart PathPosition for Segment <%1> (ID: %2)
Reason: Error due to an internal problem in the system software.
Effect: Robot reposition on path will not work.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.

msg_object: %1: Soft-Torque functionality is not available (macro %2) %3
Reason: Soft torque function is not available for this axis
Effect: Soft-Torque macro can not be executed
Parameter_3: Program name/line number in end-user program where failure occured

msg_object: Inertia Jyy for joint %1 must not be negative
Reason: Inertia Jyy for joint must not be negative.
Effect: Calculated torque model cannot be used.
Solution: Check the configuration of the torque model.

msg_object: Function '%1' is not available %3
Reason: Function is not available.
Effect: Desired function has not been executed.
Parameter_2: Program name/linen umber in end-user program where failure occured.

msg_object: %1': time out homing (%2)
Reason: A time out expired during the homing sequence.
Effect: The homing seuqence is aborted. The axis is not referenced.
Solution: Homing has to be done again.

msg_object: Cannot read from EEProm - simulation mode is active
Reason: cannot read eeprom-

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x004F Mailbox VoE).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Setting kinematic <%1> (ID %2) on path <%3> (ID %4) leads to a leap.
Reason: Application error: A kinematic has been set to a position which differs from its physical position.
Effect: The command will not be executed as this would cause the robot to leap. The movement of the robot cannot be continued.
Solution: Check the application program. Quit all errors and reload the program.

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0032 PLL error).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. Master not synchronized, at least one DC event received.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Type of connected handheld device (IP: %1) could not be detected, configured type: '%2'
Reason: Type of connected device is not known.
Effect: Key and LED mapping is possibly incorrect.
Solution: Check connected device and plc configuration.
Parameter_1: IP address of connected handheld device.

msg_object: Invalid joint type for joint %1 in RobotTransform
Reason: For the joint indicated an invalid joint type has been configured.
Effect: Kinematic not available. MCU cannot be started.
Solution: Check the configuration data of the kinematic.

msg_object: %1: Value '%2' for configuration entry '%3' is no multiple of '%4'.
Reason: An invalid value has been configured for an configuration entry.
Effect: The device can not operate or the ressource can not be used.
Solution: A valid value has to be configured for the configuration entry.
Parameter_1: configuration path or name of the device
Parameter_2: the invalid value configured for the configuration entry
Parameter_4: step size defined for configuration entry

msg_object: Prediction error for job %2 (ID %1): distorted by later changes in velocity %3 ms (configured limit: %4 ms).
Reason: Application error: The job prediction is wrong.
Effect: Trigger is signalled with a wrong prewarn time.
Solution: Reduce the cartesian velocity and/or acceleration round about the job position.

msg_object: %1(%2,%3): invalid symbol '%4'
Reason: syntax-error in configfile

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x002C Fatal sync error).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. Sync0 or Sync1 are not received any more.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Set slave to INIT and back to OP so that the distributed clocks are initalized again. Check the failed init command.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Signal error! Zone switch feedback 'mold area free' has a different state than expected!
Reason: Signal error! Zone switch feedback 'mold area free' has a different state than expected!

msg_object: %1: '%2': Mailbox '%3' has invalid size (act = %4, min = %5, max = %6, section = '%7' / '%8').
Reason: If the mailbox is too small, it is too small in general or it is too small for at least one of the allowed protocols. If the mailbox is too big, it is too big in general.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Solution: Adapt the size of the mailbox or allow less protocols.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object
Parameter_3: Name of mailbox with invalid size
Parameter_8: Subsection of node

msg_object: IO-Update: Update-Cycle-Time of '%1' (%2us) not multiple of IO-Update-Cycle-Time (%3us)
Reason: Cycle time of object registered in io-update is not a multiple of io-update cycle time.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1(%2,%3): invalid int value
Reason: integer-number is syntactical false

msg_object: Reset origin of application %1
%1: Homing failed %3
Target hardware %1 not supported yet (%2).
Reason: target hardware is not yet supported

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0012 Unknown requested state).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. The requested state is not defined
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Do only request the defined states. Check the failed init command.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: The workpiece %1 has a negative workpiece radius (%2)
Reason: The radius of a workpiece must not be negative

msg_object: PCB Add (part %1): hwRevision: %2
Reason: Second part of generic PCB-Add message

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Out of memory (%4)
Reason: Ther is not enough memory to compile the project successfully.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.
Solution: Unloading of other projects; increasing of the TC- or UOS-heap.

msg_object: %1: Jogging not possible due to active limit switches.
Reason: At least one limit-switch of a robot-joints is active.

msg_object: %1: DC System time difference violation (expected max (+/-)%2 ns, actual = %3 ns).
Reason: DC System time difference (BRD on register 0x92C) is not within expected range.
Effect: Error in synchronisation of distributed Clocks.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object.
Parameter_2: Expected maximum DC system time difference

msg_object: %1: Force to value %2 (source=%3)
Reason: Force activation for an input or output.
Effect: Input or output works with force value (for inputs force value is visible in applications, for outputs force value is transfered to hardware).
Parameter_1: Configured name or configuration-path of input or output.
Parameter_2: New force value for input or output
Parameter_3: Source of force action (appl or tool)

msg_object: Kinematic %1 (Joint %2): Setting position not possible. Drive is not referenced.
Reason: The position cannot be set when the actual position of the drive is not available. The drive signals 'reference lost' by its status bit.
Effect: The joint's position has not been set.
Solution: Before setting the position of a joint the drive must be referenced or the status bit 'reference lost' has to be cleared.

msg_object: Invalid joint type <%1>
Reason: An invalid joint type has been configured.
Effect: The corresponding kinematic is not available.

msg_object: %1: Hot connect.
Reason: Hot connect device was added to the EtherCAT segment.
Effect: The hot connect device is now available.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1: Invalid status word (0x%3) received from axis %2
Reason: Communication error or device malfuntion
Solution: Check communication between control system and drive; Contact drive vendor

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0015 Invalid mailbox configuration (BOOTSTRAP)).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state. Mismatch between ESI and firmware regarding the BOOTSTRAP mailbox sync manager configuration.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Use the correct ESI-Firmware combination. Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Trigger '%1' has been ignored since this is the first path-segment %3
%1: KTY Failure cleared.
Reason: Clearing message for error 6. The internal problem of the low level driver ceased.
Parameter_1: configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %8 Joint velocity exceeds limit by %1 %%, base joint: %2; value: %3, limit: %4, motion command (%5) %6, parameter %7
Reason: A violation of the specified limit has been detected.
Solution: Reduce the velocity in the program or raise the configured limit.
Parameter_5: Position number of the segment in the path
Parameter_8: Main run or in look-ahead problem

msg_object: %1: Jogging is not permitted (active main mode: %2).
Reason: Jogging is not permitted.
Solution: Check system state (releases, drive state, pending errors, ...)

msg_object: Incompatible version of PCALL header files (%1). At least version %2 required
Reason: The system contains the wrong version of TeachTalk header files
Effect: No application program can be started.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.
Parameter_1: Version string of the header files

msg_object: Single joint limiter ON: %1, parameter: %2
Reason: Message is issued upon activation of single joint limiter.
Solution: Reduce dynamic values in the motion program.
Parameter_2: Segment parameter where single joint limiter became active

msg_object: '%1': Feed Belt %2 Error (%3).
Reason: The Feed Belt of the Infeed is in error state.
Parameter_3: error ID of the Feed Belt

msg_object: Robot %1: McuApplyServo failed in ApplyDrive %3
Reason: call of McuApplyServo returned false
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: PCB Remove (part %1): printNr: %2, serialNr: %3
Reason: Fourth part of PCB-Remove message

msg_object: No resources left to register Prog:%1, Vers:%2 at TCP (socket %3)
Reason: (internal): PRCLib problem: TCP service for registration of server not available
Effect: no communication with rpc/tcp socket possible
Solution: Supply system resources and restart server manager. If problems continues, contact vendor.

msg_object: cannot read from file %1, handle %2, elementsize %3, elementcount %4
Reason: Cannot read from repsys file. Maybe the file is corrupted.

msg_object: Drive %1 could not be created - unknown type of drive (catalog-path: %2)
Reason: the creation of a drive-instance for a configured drive has failed - the type of the drive couldn't be identified

msg_object: %1: %2: SII access not allowed (section = '%3' / '%4').
Reason: SII is accessed during a state transition, which does not allow this access.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Can't read string-value '%1.%2'
Reason: String entry cannot be read

msg_object: Internal error: RtTranslateBusAddress failed, busAddr %1.%2 lasterror=%3
Reason: error in translation of bus relative address

msg_object: error adding protocol %1 to reportsystem
Reason: The new repsys-protocol cannot successfully added to the repsys

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): User-object is expected
Reason: An object with the USER attribute is expected at this position.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: TeachControl is not running (actual state: '%1')!
Reason: TeachControl is not running.
Effect: Robot functions can not be executed.

msg_object: %1: Node address %2 not found in projection.
Reason: A node address, which does not match any node address in the projection, was configured.
Effect: The operation of the slave is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: '%1': Diagnostic message '%2'
Reason: New diagnostic message

msg_object: Cannot create File %1
Reason: Statusreport can not open specified file
Parameter_1: File name which cannot be created

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0017 Invalid sync manager configuration).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. Sync manager configuration is not valid.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0015 Invalid mailbox configuration (BOOTSTRAP)).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. Mismatch between ESI and firmware regarding the BOOTSTRAP mailbox sync manager configuration.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Use the correct ESI-Firmware combination. Check the failed init command.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Kinematic %3 (ID %4) has no inverse transformation implemented for %1 (ID %2)
Reason: The selected robot type can only handle PTP motion commands.
Effect: Cartesian motion commands will be ignored.
Solution: Use PTP commands only or use different kinematic.

msg_object: ACB Callback Error: %1
Reason: Specified callback function caused an error.

msg_object: Trying to unregister at already released object (%1) ID %2 (%3)
Reason: Error due to an internal problem in the system software.
Effect: Context sensitive. Look at additional messages.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.

msg_object: %1: The text for configuration entry '%2' has an invalid length (min %3, max %4 characters).
Reason: The text configured for a configuration entry is too short or too long.
Effect: The device can not operate or the ressource can not be used.
Solution: A valid value has to be configured for the configuration entry.
Parameter_1: configuration path or name of the device

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): No routine
Reason: The given identifier is not a routine.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: The default tool of robot '%1' has been modified %3
Reason: Internal error in tool handling. The data of the default tool has been changed.
Effect: Data of default tool could be incorrect.
Solution: Send a statusreport to your system integrator.
Parameter_2: Programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1: InputPreparationTime %2ns is beyond its limits (%3ns - %4ns).
Reason: The InputPreparationTime is not within the possible range.
Effect: The correct operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Solution: Increase the cycle time of the EtherCAT slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object.

msg_object: Reference system <%1> of configured REFSYS:%2 not found in database
Reason: Application error: The specified reference system could not be found in the database.
Parameter_2: Number of the configured reference system

msg_object: Stopped application %1 (Reason: %2)
%1: SDO (index: 0x%2 subindex: %3) aborted by server: 0x05040005 (Out of memory)
Reason: SDO transfer has been aborted by SDO server (the CANOpen device).
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module

msg_object: Statusreport Destinationpath same as Temporarypath %1
'%1': Maximum number of products (%2) have been exceeded ('%3').
Reason: The maximum number of products have been exceeded.

msg_object: %1: Timeout on waiting for response of a request. %3
Reason: Request was not answered within given timeout.
Effect: Request not finished, returnvalue will be -1.
Solution: Ensure IEC application responses all requests, or increase timeout.

msg_object: cart. orientation velocity
Reason: Additional information

msg_object: Can't read real-value '%1.%2'
Reason: Real entry cannot be read

msg_object: %1 could not be created
%1: Internal error: Missing ID for file segment %3
Reason: No file segment ID has been given.
Parameter_2: Program name/line number in end-user program where failure occured

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Types of exported variables must not contain references
Reason: The type of the exported variable contains references.
Effect: The project cannot be compiled without errors.

msg_object: Given project is not valid in macro: 'LoadProgram'. %3
Reason: The given project in the macro 'LoadProgram' does not exist, or is invalid.
Solution: Check if project name is correct.
Parameter_1: Project/program and line number at which the error occurs

msg_object: Unable to execute '%1' - robot is in mold closure area %3
Reason: Robot is in mold closure area
Parameter_1: Program name/line number in enduser program where failure occured.

msg_object: %1: Receive-Fifo full - Receive Overflow
Reason: Error at receive-callback
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the CAN-channel

Reason: A Node has an error.
Effect: The transport system switches to the Error state and a Reset command is sent to the transport sysetm

msg_object: Encoder position object %1 has been created, but endpoint-mapping failed
Program cannot be started due to a missing safety release.
Reason: Safety release is missing.

msg_object: %1: LSS/LMT: Error setting node-Id, error %2 specific %3
Reason: slave reports error for producer during configurating of node-number
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module
Parameter_3: Specific error according to LSS/LMT description

msg_object: '%1': Communication Link Error Path '%2' ('%3')
Reason: A Path has an communication link error.
Effect: The transport system switches to the Error state and a Reset command is sent to the transport sysetm

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0024 Invalid input mapping).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. Input process data mapping does not match the expected mapping.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1: Internal Reference Sensor configured but external Reference Sensor used
Reason: The currently used reference sensor does not comply with the configured reference sensor
Solution: Check why hardware construction and configuration dont match
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of the affected device

msg_object: Drive %1: wrong state for resetting reference bit %3
Reason: wrong state for resetting reference bit (only for Lenze-drives)
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1.%2 Line %3%4: LookAhead-Limiter (impact or overthrow) - %5%% of prog. velocity (SegNr %6)
Reason: User information about look-ahead limiter (Limitation due to fence overthrow or impact energy).
Parameter_5: Ratio of reduced velocity to programmed maximum velocity

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Internal parser error (stack overflow)
Reason: Internal message.

msg_object: '%1': Command '%2' has been rejected. Command state:'%3' ('%4')
Reason: The specified command was rejected.

msg_object: Invalid overlap data: path %1 (ID %2), segment position on path: %3.
Reason: Application error: Overlapping could not be calculated for given overlap data. Check overlap definition.
Effect: Overlapping of movements not possible. Robot and motion program are stopped.
Parameter_3: Position of segment in the path

msg_object: End position of segment %1 lies in nogo-area %2 with guard point %4 of %3%6 of kinematic %5
Reason: A kinematic has encountered a segment whose end position lies in a  blocked area.
Solution: Change end position of respective segment.
Parameter_6: Name of object containing the guard point, e.g a tool, if existent

msg_object: TeachControl system project is not operational!
Reason: TeachControl system project is not operational.
Effect: Robot functions can not be executed.

msg_object: Area '%1' could not be created, max. allowed number of areas (%2) is already present
Reason: Too many active areas.

msg_object: %1: LSS/LMT: Cannot access device, action %2 code %3
Reason: couldnt send message
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module

msg_object: %1: Corresponding conveyor could not be mapped.
Reason: The conveyor connected with this tracking object could not be mapped.
Solution: Contact your system supplier in case of recurrence.

msg_object: <%1> is not possible - %2 check(s) already active (max. %3)
Reason: Check function cannot be called, because the maximum number of checks is already reached.
Solution: Terminate all active checks, or wait until one check is finished.

msg_object: %1: received invalid real number ('%2')
Reason: external device sent a real number containing invalid bits
Effect: received data is ignored and 0 is transmitted

msg_object: %1: position control. Error Code: %2
Reason: Extra-function-control emergency reported by CANOpen-drive DS402
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the axis

msg_object: Tried to set too many joints (%1, max 8) in RobotTransform
Reason: Too many joints have been specified for a kinematic.
Effect: Kinematic not available. MCU cannot be started.
Solution: Check the configuration data of the kinematic.

msg_object: Deviation (%4) of tracking delta geometry of additional position %3 of kinematic %1 exceeds configured maximal deviation (%5) at %2.
Reason: During tracking the geometric deviation between the predicted and the actual additional position of the robot exceeds the allowed maximal deviation. Probably the tracking signal is of low quality or the configured maximal deviation is too small or there is an error in the controller software.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.
Solution: Check conveyor signal or increase configured maximal deviation or contact your vendor.
Parameter_4: Deviation of tracking delta geometry of the additional position

msg_object: %1 named %2 timed out after %3 seconds (kinematic %4)
Reason: An autostop-object has not been deactivated within its time-out period.
Effect: The robot transits to emergency stop.
Solution: Deactivate autostop-object in time or increase time-out.

msg_object: Functionblock '%1' can not be created during runtime.
Reason: FB is declared as local variable in function or method (or VAR_TEMP).
Effect: Object isn't useable in that local scope.
Solution: Object resp. its owner has to be declared globally.

msg_object: %1: Robotbase not appropriate when using simplified cartesian positions (invalid configuration)
Opening kernel driver %1 failed, last error %2.
Reason: kernel driver cannot be opened

msg_object: Robot movement not possible, because of an open safety door
Reason: Not all safety doors are closed

msg_object: %1: StopRobot can't be used while robot is tracking %3
Reason: StopRobot has been called while tracking was active.
Solution: Check program, stop tracking before executing StopRobot.
Parameter_2: Program name/line number in enduser program where failure occured

msg_object: couldn't start housekeeper
Reason: couldn't start housekeeper

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x0031 Invalid DC latch configuration).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. DC latch configuration is invalid due to application requirements.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): External Mapping failed : '%4'
Reason: The mapping to a firmware function with MAPX failed.
Solution: Check if firmware function (PCall) is available an the signature correspondends.

msg_object: Kinematic %3 (ID %4) is singular at %1 %2
Reason: The kinematic cannot move to the specified position, because this leads to a singularity.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.

msg_object: Kin. %1 is leaving work joints area %4 with joint %5 (position %6) while executing motion command %2 (param. %3)
Reason: User error: Robot leaves a work joints area
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped
Solution: Change the motion program or the direction of motion
Parameter_4: Name of the work joints area

msg_object: %1: Device Temperature. Error Code: %2
Reason: temperature of module too high or too low
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module

msg_object: Configured axis-filter type %1 not available
Reason: Configuration error: An invalid filter type has been configured.

msg_object: %1: cartesian jogging rejected %3
Reason: cartesian jogging rejected by main mode manager

msg_object: Basic directories do not exist or have no teachtalk-fileentry
Reason: Basic directories  ('_system.tt', '_base.tt', <libPath>)  do not exist or have no teachtalk-fileentry
Solution: Supply an application or set the configuration value applNecessary to 0

msg_object: %1.%2: Position check is not possible, as base system is not mapped %3
Reason: Base reference system for position which should be checked is not mapped
Parameter_3: Program name/line number in end-user program where problem occured

msg_object: Drive %1: error launched %3
Reason: error launched
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1(%2,%3): include file '%4' not found
Reason: config-file not found

msg_object: Error create SMemAdInstance ErrCode: %1
Reason: firmware error

msg_object: The tool %1 cannot be appended to a workpiece
Reason: Within a chain a workpiece must not be followed by a tool
Solution: Within a chain first the tool and than the workpiece must be programmed

msg_object: %1: Program execution not possible due to a blockedspace violation.
Reason: Robot has entered blockedspace.

msg_object: Internal error: Device %1.%2 (device %3, function %4) interrupt line %5 is not a PCI interrupt line.
Reason: PCI device has a assigned interrupt line that is not a PCI interrupt line

msg_object: %1: Velocity limited guards are not available for robot '%2'
Reason: Dynamic monitoring for guards is not available (configured) for this robot.

msg_object: Wrong joint type (%1) configured for rotational joint %2
Reason: Configuration error: the joint type is wrong.
Effect: Kinematic cannot be used. Motion program cannot be started.
Solution: Check the configuration data of the specified joint of the kinematic.

msg_object: %1: '%2': The number of nodes '%3' is invalid (act = %4, min = %5, max = %6, section = '%7' / '%8').
Reason: The number of nodes is invalid.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object
Parameter_3: Name of node with invalid number
Parameter_8: Subsection of node

msg_object: file handle usage over 90%%
Effect: It could lead to an exception, if additional files are opened.

msg_object: Size of memory object ('%1': %3) differs from expected size (%2)
Reason: Invalid memory object size (e.g. unexpected shared memory size, invalid buffer size, ...)
Parameter_2: expected size of the memory object
Parameter_3: actual size of the memory object

msg_object: Invalid acceleration reduction profile in path %1 (ID %2).
Reason: Application error: An invalid acceleration profile has been assigned to a path.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.

msg_object: %8 Position of virtual joint %2 exceeds limit (%4); value: %3, motion command (%5) %6, parameter %7
Reason: The position limit of a virtual joint has been violated.
Solution: Modify the path or the configuration of the limit.
Parameter_5: Position number of the segment in the path
Parameter_8: Main run or look-ahead problem

msg_object: %1: linking failed - application version %2 does not match runtime version %3
Reason: application code file does not match runtime system
Solution: check if application linked with matching runtime system frame code

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0024 Invalid input mapping).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state. Input process data mapping does not match the expected mapping.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Robot %1 is powered - Enable MoveByHand not allowed
Reason: Robot is powered

msg_object: %2: IMM output signal '%1' is not available %3
Reason: Signal is not available.
Effect: Requested operation can not be executed.
Parameter_3: Program name/line number in enduser program where failure occured.

msg_object: %1: Error in device software (Error register: %2)
Reason: see manual of device
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the group

msg_object: PCB Add (part %1): funcVar: %2
Reason: Third part of generic PCB-Add message

msg_object: Wrist-joint position %1 has joints offset or moving reference system.
Reason: Error in application program. Wrist joint positions are not allowed for tracking systems.
Effect: No tracking available with this position type.

msg_object: reading Uos ChangeMsgqueue failed, expected %1 bytes, read %2 bytes
Reason: reading msgqueue failed

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0037 DC Sync1 cycle time).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state. DC sync1 cycle time does not fit to the application requirements.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: External emergency stop active! Robot movement not possible.
Reason: External emergency stop was pressed
Effect: Robot stopped and programs can not be continued

Reason: syntax-error in cofig-file

msg_object: %1: Set values from PLC are ignored by drive (%2).
Reason: Parameter 0x28F1 is not set to 'DS402' (value: 2).
Parameter_2: value of parameter 0x28F1 read from drive

msg_object: IO-Update: Update-Cycle-Time of '%1' (%2us) not multiple of System-Tick (%3us)
Reason: Cycle time of object registered in io-update is not a multiple of system tick time.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1(%2,%3): internal parser error (terminal symbol)
Reason: intern error

msg_object: %1: Referencesystem '%2' couldn't be set as actual system %3
Reason: Given reference system couldn't be set
Parameter_3: Program name / line number in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1: Jogging not possible due to a not pressed enabling switch (active main mode: %2).
Reason: Safety release was not granted to the robot.

msg_object: Position %1.ApplyTrackPos(%2) is not reachable. (%3)
Reason: The given position is not reachable on the tracking object. The tracking limits could not be applied.
Effect: The tracking object can not be used any more.
Solution: Check if the given position is reachable on the object. Probably the orientation of the position is wrong too.
Parameter_3: Program name/line number in end-user program where the problem occured.

msg_object: %1': maximum software position limit of drive (%3 (%4)) is more restrictive than in PLC (%2)
Reason: The maximum (positive) software position limit of the drive is less than positive software position limit of PLC.
Solution: The parameter for the software position limits of the axis and of the drive have to be checked.
Parameter_3: configured limit of drive [units of control]
Parameter_4: configured limit of drive [units of drive]

msg_object: Internal error: Restoring config space image of device %1 function %2 failed
Reason: restoring config space dump has failed

msg_object: %1: Object can not be used for tracking %3
Reason: Object can not be used for tracking (e.g. because object has been marked as not processable by ApplyTrackPos)
Effect: Tracking using this object is not possible
Parameter_2: Program name/line number in end-user program where problem occured

msg_object: %1: SDO (index: 0x%2 subindex: %3) aborted by server: 0x08000020 (Data cannot be transferred or stored to the application)
Reason: SDO transfer has been aborted by SDO server (the CANOpen device).
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module

msg_object: Start key for '%1' ignored, since '%2' is already running
Reason: A stroke on start key has been ignored, since a program/function is already running

msg_object: Orientation of %1 (ID %2) not reachable by kinematic %3 (ID %4)
Reason: A programmed orientation cannot be reached by a kinematic.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.
Solution: Modify the motion program such that the orientation can be reached by the kinematic.

msg_object: Kinematic %1: Invalid compensator on joint %2. Compensators are only supported for main joints.
Reason: A compensator has been specified for a joint which does not support it.
Solution: Check configuration data of dynamic model.

msg_object: Non Maskable Interrupt (NMI) (bp=%1, pc=%2, regs=%3)
Reason: NMI occured

msg_object: Unit '%1' couldn't be attached to a robot
Reason: No robot could be deduced for this unit

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Wrong string-length
Reason: The length of a string can be 0 to 255 characters.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: %1: no cyclic data received
Reason: no new message since last update
Effect: PDO, endoints and device will be set do error state.
Solution: Check connection to the device, state of the device and parametration of the PDOs. If this error message occures repeated try to increase the cycle time and/or baud rate. A CAN bus record may help to identify the detailed error reason.
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0052 External hardware not ready).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state. External connection to another device or signal is missing.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: <McuTerminateMotionBuffer> not possible - transfer of motion-buffer (ID: %1) is active
Reason: Application error: The command McuTerminateMotionBuffer must not be called in case transferring the motion buffer is currently active.
Solution: Send command McuTerminateMotionBuffer earlier or avoid sending it at all.

msg_object: '%1': invalid parameter %2 (%3) %4
Reason: A parameter of a FB is invalid.
Solution: Check the parameter of the FB

msg_object: The configured Denavit-Hartenberg parameter %1 of joint %2 has the invalid value %3
Reason: Configuration error: a configured DH parameter of a joint is invalid.
Effect: Kinematic cannot be used. Motion program cannot be started.
Solution: Check configured DH parameters of the specified joint of the kinematic.

msg_object: The tool of robot '%1' used to calculate actual position is invalid, instead tool '%2' is used.
Reason: Internal error in tool handling. The selected tool is invalid.
Effect: Default tool or Flange is set instead.
Solution: Send a statusreport to your system integrator.
Parameter_2: Name of tool which is set instead

msg_object: Window for PTP pick&place segment %1 is not a principal plane at %2
Reason: Application error: Window is not a principal plane.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.
Solution: Change coordinates of window so that it is in a principal plane.

msg_object: %1: Path tracking (reference system: '%2') is not possible with orientation interpolation mode '%4' %3
Reason: Path tracking is not possible with the selected orientation interpolation mode.
Parameter_3: Program name / line number in end-user program where failure occured.

msg_object: '%1': Product jam downstream '%2' (%3).
Reason: A sensor did not detect the end of a product (no falling edge).
Solution: Possible reasons are: a product jam downstream or a sensor malfunction.

msg_object: %1: Order #%2 couldn't be fetched because of an empty order-list %3
Failure during setup of robot %1
Reason: errors occured while setting up a configured robot

msg_object: Needed configuration missing: %1
Slave robot tries to use an invalid master TCP (%1)
Reason: Error in application program: A master has to have a valid Cartesian TCP position when used. Maybe the interpolation for the master robot is not started or no forward transformation is configured.

msg_object: Int-value '%1.%2' out of range [%3..%4]
Reason: Integer value out of range

msg_object: Can't allocate memory
Reason: (internal) out of heap memory
Solution: supply more heap memory, contact vendor

msg_object: %1: Too many PDOs for actual number of nodes: (PDO-No.: %2 nodes: %3)
Reason: Couldnt install PDO
Parameter_1: configured name or hardware configuration path of the module
Parameter_3: Actual number of installed CANopen nodes

msg_object: Invalid dynamics data %1 (ID %2), component group %3.
Reason: Application or user error. A dynamics object containing invalid data has been created.
Effect: Invalid dynamics leads to program abortion.

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Invalid expression
Reason: The expression is invalid.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: %1: auto pci configuration not possible, there is more than one device of that type
Reason: There are more pci devices of that type in system. Auto configuration for pci devices is only possible if there is only one device of a type in system. It must be pointed out, that internal pci device (e.g. network controller) are also included at checking auto configuration.
Effect: Distinct identification of the pci device is not possible as well as operation.
Solution: Pci configuration (slot and if applicable bus) must be used in config file.
Parameter_1: configuration path or name of the device

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): invalid usage of externally mapped function
Reason: An externally mapped function is used with START or DO.
Effect: Can occur during operation of the control-software.

msg_object: %1(%2,%3): entry '%4' exists, overwritten
Reason: there already exists an entry with this name; it will be overwritten

msg_object: RcPackInterface <%1> is not activated
Reason: interface at plc not activated

msg_object: Project %1 / Pass %2
Reason: Marks the begin of a compiler pass.

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = 0x000E License error).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave. HW/SW license invalid or evaluation period expired.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Contact slave manufacturer. Check the failed init command.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1: Not able to operate with device firmware version %2. Update at least to %3.
Reason: The control firmware needs to operate at least with the suggested device firmware version to ensure correct functionality.
Solution: Update firmware to the suggested version.
Parameter_1: configuration path or name of the device

msg_object: Internal error: '%1' already selected, but selecting flow (id %2) does not exist (any more), program '%3' stopped
Reason: The flow, which selected the robot is invalid

msg_object: firmwareVersion is configured - that is not allowed
Reason: firmwareVersion is configured

msg_object: %1: supply error gone (%2)
Reason: A problem with a voltage supply has gone
Effect: The module or endpoint that was affected works again
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object or endpoint
Parameter_2: Description or type of the supply that causes the problem

msg_object: %1: nullpulse error
Reason: Zero-pulse monitoring is not configured correct or incremental encoder is faulty.
Solution: Configuration and incremental encoder should be checked.
Parameter_1: Name or hardware configuration path of module

msg_object: %1: Backward movement completed, start position of path reached (movement time forward: %2ms, distance traveled: %3mm)
Reason: The backward movement was successfully completed. Further backward movement is not possible, as the start position of the path has been reached.
Effect: The backward movement was successfully completed
Parameter_2: Duration of the backward movement (time required by the corresponding path section during the forward movement)

msg_object: Torque of drive %2 exceeds limits even if stopped on path at %1
Reason: The torque limit of the given drive is exceeded even if stopped on path at the given path position. This happens due to tracking or gravity.
Effect: It could be possible to pass the given path position without exceeding the torque limits but it is not possible to stop and therefore it is dangerous to try to pass the position.
Solution: Increase the torque limit or reduce the tracking velocity.

msg_object: Creation of statereport %1 has been started
Kinematic %1: McuStopJoints failed %3
Reason: call of McuStopJoints returned false
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: Kinematic %1 could not be created.
Reason: Due to a configuration error the kinematic could not be created

msg_object: file handle usage is ok
PCall '%1 (%2)' failed (%3, %4)
Reason: A PCall failed.
Parameter_3: instance name (e.g. name of the axis, name of the IO device, ... )

msg_object: %2: Shared memory for moving reference system #%1 couldn't be accessed %3
Teaching path parameter for '%1' not possible since robot '%2' ist not on path %3
Reason: The robot is not on path. this happens, e.g., after a StopJoints.
Parameter_3: program name/line number in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0007 Firmware update not successful. Old firmware still running).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state. Error occurred during firmware update.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Read user manual or contact slave manufacturer. Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Kinematic %1: Invalid previous joint number (%2) of joint %3 in kinematic chain
Reason: The position of a joint within the kinematic chain is invalid.

msg_object: %1: Message queue overflow (%2).
Reason: A message queue overflow occurred.
Parameter_1: Detailed information about where the error occurred

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Types are not compatible
Reason: The given types are not compatible.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.
Solution: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: Invalid number of columns (%1) (must be %2) of Jacobi matrix in transform function %3 of robot %4
Reason: Error due to an internal problem in the system software.
Effect: Kinematic cannot be used. Motion program cannot be started.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.
Parameter_1: Number of lines in the Jacobian
Parameter_2: Correct number of lines for the Jacobian

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Division by zero
Reason: A number is devided by zero.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: TCP position is not calculable for position '%1' of robot '%2'
Reason: From the given position it is not possible to calculate the TCP position for this robot.

msg_object: %1: '%2': Node '%3' has invalid value '%4' (section = '%5' / '%6').
Reason: The node in the XML file has an invalid value.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Program with SAVE PROJECT variables already exists in project %4
Reason: A program already exists with a SAVE PROJECT variable of the same name. The unambiguousness of the data file is not assured.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: Invalid path position: path %1 (ID %2), motion command %3 (ID %4), parameter %5.
Reason: Error in application program.

msg_object: Unable to remove object '%2' from ArrayList '%1'
Reason: Internal error, an object could not been removed from an ArrayList

msg_object: %1: Internal errror: No axis connected (routine: %2, axis index: %3)
Reason: The single axis is not internally connected to any axis.
Effect: The single axis cannot be used.
Solution: Get in contact with your system integrator.
Parameter_2: Name of routine in which error occurred.

msg_object: When calling <%2> kinematic <%1> must be in state <stoppedJoints>.
Reason: Application error. For execution of the desired command the robot must be in state <stoppedJoints>

msg_object: Robot %1: implausible start values for referenced drives rejected %3
Reason: start-value for drive not plausible, because out of working-range
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

Reason: The application has a syntactic error. The compiler expects the given string on this position.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: %1: Jogging not possible, because interpolator for drive set values is not running.
Reason: Mc interpolator for set values is not running.
Solution: Start mc interpolator for set values.

msg_object: Detected defect fan device %1
Reason: defect fan device

msg_object: %1: Unexpected size of Shared Memory '%2': %3 (expected: %4)
Reason: Internal error, size of already existing shared memory, which was created by another master, differs from local expected size.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: '%1': Command 'Exit parameterization level ' failed.
Reason: The axis could not be set to the operating mode.
Effect: The axis is not ready for operation.
Solution: Check the axis configuration, especially the resolution settings

msg_object: %1: Several main mode managers are attached to single axes.
Reason: The configuration flag 'usedBySingleAxis' is set for several main mode managers.
Effect: System may not behave as expected.

msg_object: Kinematic <%1>: Input drive position out of range of nonlinear gear table (drive: %2 pos: %3).
Reason: The gear table has a too small drive range
Solution: Define gear table for a bigger drive range

msg_object: Command <%1> sent to non-registered kinematic <%2> (ID %3)
Reason: Application error: The command indicated cannot be executed before the kinematic has been registered at the execution unit.

msg_object: Invalid %3. parameter (%4) in overlap data %1 (ID %2).
Reason: Application or user error. An invalid overlap parameter has been used for overlapping.
Effect: Movement overlapping does not work. Program is stopped.
Solution: Check the application and  the overlap data.

msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0035 DC Invalid sync cycle time).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: A new provider (prefix: '%1', TLP: '%2') collides with the existing provider (prefix: '%3', TLP: '%4').
Reason: Top level path (TLP) is already in use by the existing provider. It is not possible that the new provider uses this TLP too.
Effect: The new provider cannot be added to Varaible Server.

msg_object: McuReleaseDbObj: object with ID %1 has already been released
Reason: Application error: A database object can either be of type eMcuPermanent or eMcuTemp. If it is permanent this message occurs if the object has been released more often than once. If it is temporary this message occurs every time the object is released, because there is no need to release it.

msg_object: %1 files compiled
Reason: Informs how many files have been compiled.

msg_object: %1: Init command '%2' failed during state transition '%3' (AL Status Code = %4 Vendor specific).
Reason: An init command failed during a state transition of the EtherCAT slave.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the effected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration path or name of object

msg_object: Kinematic %1: Invalid gear linkage on drive %2. Gear linkages are only supported for rotational joints.
Reason: A non-linear drive has bee specified for a joint that does not support it.

msg_object: Internal error in flow management - Program '%1' (flow-id: %2) is missing in flow-table
Reason: internal error

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Unexpected usage of program '%4'
Reason: The usage of a program is not allowed at this position.
Effect: Application can not be compiled without errors.

msg_object: %1 switches tracking logger off: NextSegNr: %2, TrackObj: %3, samples: %4, overflow: %5
Reason: The tracking logger has finished logging a tracking segment.

msg_object: '%1': Sensor of Correction Belt %2 Error (%3).
Reason: The Sensor of a Correction Belt of the Infeed is in an Error state.

msg_object: The actual path speed on segment '%1' is too low (actual: %2 mm/s, programmed: %3 mm/s)
Reason: path-speed observation has detected a shortfall of minimum path-speed
Solution: check programmed path and it's dynamic

msg_object: Invalid lock on data base object: %1 (ID %2)
Reason: Error due to an internal problem in the system software.
Effect: Context sensitive. Look at additional messages.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.

msg_object: %1 (%2/%3): Warning : %4 %5 not referenced
Reason: The specified element is not referenced anywhere in the application.
Solution: Check if the element can be removed from the application.

msg_object: Login in application %1
Kinematic %1: Invalid mount point (%3 = %4) for linkage on drive %2
Reason: When specifying a non-linear drive an invalid mount point has been used.

msg_object: Internal error: %1, %2, %3, %4
Reason: An internal error occurred.

msg_object: Initialization of deadtime-filter '%1' failed - filter time has to be greater than 0
Reason: Deadtime-filter could not been initialized

msg_object: Kinematic %1 (Joint %2): Mastering not possible. Invalid gear ratio.
Reason: The drive cannot be mastered as the gear ratio is not a whole number.
Effect: The drive has not been mastered.

msg_object: %1: Executing movement command not possible because torque is reduced for at least one axis %3
Reason: Reduced torque is active.
Effect: Movement command can not be executed.
Parameter_2: Program name/line number in end-user program where failure occured.

msg_object: Invalid Path in Function <%1> of segment <%2> (ID: %3)
Reason: Application error: A path position with an invalid path has been passed to a function.

msg_object: %1: FMMUs %2 and %3 overlap
Reason: The logical address ranges of the two FMMUs overlap. If bit addresses are used, there must be at least 3 fill bytes in between. If these fill bytes do not exist, the message class is error. In any other case the message class is warning.
Effect: Operation of the object is not possible.
Parameter_1: Configuration entry or name of EtherCAT slave
Parameter_3: Index of FMMU overlapping the first

msg_object: TrackingLogger on: SegNr: %1, TrsfID: %2 %3
Reason: The tracking logger has started to log a tracking segment.

msg_object: Prediction job %2 (ID %1) not possible - connecting with LookAheadBuffer failed.
Reason: Error due to an internal problem in the system software: Trigger job with prewarn time is not possible because of a problem with look-ahead buffer.
Effect: Trigger with prewarn time do not work.
Solution: Provide information to your distributor: Create a Status Report and e-mail it to your distributor.

msg_object: Invalid waiting time %3 in overlap data %1 (ID %2).
Reason: Application or user error. An overlap has been assigned an invalid waiting time.
Effect: Waiting time between two motion commands will be discarded.

msg_object: %1: no forward transformation %3
Reason: no forward transformation
Parameter_2: programname/linenumber in enduserprogram where failure occured

msg_object: Sum of wrist joints exceeds limit; value: %1, limit: %2, motion command (%3) %4, parameter %5
Reason: Application error. A violation of the sum of wrist joints has been detected. The path must be modified.
Effect: Robot and motion program are stopped.
Solution: Increase sum of wrist joints limit in the configuration or modify program.
Parameter_2: Limit for sum of wrist joints
Parameter_3: Position number of segment in the path
